snippet.textDisplay: KUBICA IS BACK ON TOP
snippet.textOriginal: KUBICA IS BACK ON TOP

snippet.textDisplay:
From Italian motorsport by Franco Nugnes:
The Pole ended the first day of the second collective test session in Barcelona at the top of the timesheet with Alfa Romeo: of course Robert had C5 tires, an empty tank and a Ferrari engine in a rather pushed mode, but his lap it has a symbolic value that is worth a fairy tale and that F1 does not value.

Agree with the C5 soft compound tires, agree with the almost empty tank, agree with the power unit in qualifying mode, but Robert Kubica's performance cannot be out of order.
The only test driver who drove in the first day of collective tests of the second winter test session was the fastest with the Alfa Romeo C39. And it only took half a day for the Pole to place his paw and no longer be threatened by anyone up there on the top of the times list with that 1'16 ”942.

For Robert it must have been a satisfaction that pays him back for years of sacrifice. Because Kubica feels inside himself the champion who could have fought for the world championship before that damned accident at the Ronde di Andora 2011 defaced him in physique, but not in morale.
Formula 1 must not forget this day. It cannot and must not be reduced to one episode. Of course Kimi Raikkonen with the same Alfa Romeo C39 last week had hoisted himself at the top of the table of the first day, but there were only single-seaters at the debut that did not look for performance to discover their potential but had worked for reliability.
Now we have machines that are in full metamorphosis in view of Australia and the pretactic finds the time it finds. Each team follows its own schedule, without chasing the others, as it should be, but Robert's lap has satisfied the technicians of the Hinwil team.

An authoritative exponent of the team appreciated the fact that the Pole knew how to manage the soft compound in T1 to still have a good grip in T3, where many arrive, however, with the tire already finished. Robert's experience is one of the bags that Alfa Romeo will be able to take advantage of this year in the hope of going back to the top of the Manufacturers' championship, after falling to eighth place.
And this day perhaps repays Kubica of a season, that of last year, in which he was humiliated by the worst Williams in history. And you had to play last place on the grid with George Russell, a young man with good hopes who was not talented enough to stand in front of the pilot with one arm, but he also needed to resort to all the "help" of the team to demonstrate to Toto Wolff that he has not "baptized" the wrong young man.
Robert never complained, proving himself a serious professional. But it must be very tough to face an entire season like Sancho Panza against the windmills. Kubica's return to F1 was supposed to be a beautiful fairy tale to write, which had to give man's value regardless of the car.
And history has finally found a happy appendix: because the driver who does not deserve to race the GPs was chased by several teams for the role of test driver, perhaps because he had an attractive budget for a company that has believed in his fairy tale.

Today Kubica has proven to be an intact pilot, despite his objective limitations. And some pebbles from the shoe have now taken off admitting that with Alfa Romeo "... the track in Barcelona now has three curves less than last year ...".
The layout of Montmelò obviously has not changed: Robert was no longer forced to partialize the gas with a car that was not on the track, but he was able to deal with certain folds in full like all the others.
It is a day that F1 must not close too quickly: Kubica is not Nikita Mazepin who last year had soared in the post-GP tests of Spain with the Mercedes W10 which then became the world champion single-seater. It was the fastest with an Alfa Romeo that will be forced to fight in the second half of the grid.
Thanks, Robert because there is still an F1 that is not only made of bolts and DAS, but also of men. And of phenomena.
